The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Vertex Cover Reconfiguration problem, which is a problem in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem is also related to computational complexity, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the problem on specific graph classes, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
